.TH "nvmem_device_read" 9 "nvmem_device_read" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
nvmem_device_read \- Read from a given nvmem device
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" nvmem_device_read
.BI "(struct nvmem_device *nvmem "  ","
.BI "unsigned int offset "  ","
.BI "size_t bytes "  ","
.BI "void *buf "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "nvmem" 12
nvmem device to read from.
.IP "offset" 12
offset in nvmem device.
.IP "bytes" 12
number of bytes to read.
.IP "buf" 12
buffer pointer which will be populated on successful read.
.SH "RETURN"
length of successful bytes read on success and negative
error code on error.
